# Intake (improve pass 2)

Brief from run 1 stands; added `improvePass2` section documenting 4 scoped fixes:

1. **No category abbreviation.** Assets/Revenue/Liability/Equity/Expense rendered in full; drop any truncation ("ass" fix).
2. **Linked-number contrast.** Blue links on dark bg swapped to accessible accent from existing palette (WCAG AA).
3. **Ledger 200 entries + scroll.** "Recent 50 entries" becomes scrollable 200-row list with pagination/per-page selector, backed by real backend data.
4. **Real backend wiring.** Ledger + accounts read only from live Node service via Flask bridge (api.michaelwegter.com); no mock fallbacks.

Feature richness remains 10. All changes are scoped polish + backend integration.

## handoff
- produced: brief.json updated with improvePass2 requirements (4 fixes: no abbrev, link contrast, ledger 200+scroll, real backend only).
- decisions: keep run-1 stack/design/slug; reuse existing tokens for contrast fix; ledger must hit live bridged Node endpoint.
